description: Numbers n such that n^3 is palindromic in base 5.
comments: Note that '626' is itself palindromic.Contains all A034474(n), n>=1, as a subset because (5^n+1)^3=5^(3n)+3*5^(2n)+3*5^n+1 is a symmetric string 100..00300..00300..001 in base 5. [From _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 31 2008]
author: _Patrick De Geest_, May 15 1998
